description:
while the city has fallen under the spell of a magical sleep MoonShadow investigates and finds a portal to a dimensional realm of dreams. After defeating three monstrous challenges he confronts the Dreamweaver.
 
'MoonShadow' the series is about a museum custodian who un wittingly inherits the 'Moonstone', a magical artifact that bestows him with supernatural abilities. Once the janitor (Aidan) learns to use the powers of the artifact he becomes a formidable superhero.
name: Requiem For a Dreamweaver

description:
Countess Erzsébet Báthory (Báthory Erzsébet in Hungarian, Alžbeta Bátoriová(-Nádasdy) in Slovak, Elżbieta Batory in Polish, 7 August (?), 1560 – 21 August, 1614), was a Hungarian countess from the renowned Báthory family.

She is considered the most infamous serial killer in Hungarian and Slovak history and is remembered as the Bloody Lady of Čachtice (Csejte), after the castle near Trenčín (Trencsén), in Royal Hungary, in present-day Slovakia, where she spent most of her life.

After her husband's death, she and her four alleged collaborators were accused of torturing and killing dozens of girls and young women. In 1610, she was imprisoned in Čachtice Castle, where she remained until her death four years later. Her nobility allowed her to avoid trial and execution. The Báthory case has inspired many stories, featuring the countess bathing in the blood of her victims in order to retain her youth. This inspired nicknames like the Blood Countess and Countess Dracula.

Now with Peter Tye, you will enjoy the whole terrible and erotic story!!

Elizabeth continues the story of her life before living death. After a hot and heavy fling with the Varcolaci, Elizabeth returns home to a willing husband and they have four children together. Her husband dies and the years pass. Elizabeth is obsessed with her aging beauty. Believing that blood is the fountain of youth, she murders young virgins and bathes in their blood. She begins to eat their flesh. Her murderous orgies earn her the name Bloody Countess. Finally, the King of Hungary orders her arrest. Though her accomplices are executed, she is imprisoned in her castle. She dies at the age of 54, but in the womb of the earth she is reborn to the shadow world of the undead. As she emerges from her tomb, the Varcolaci is waiting for her. To his surprise, she eagerly attacks him and sucks his blood. This series is truly the deepest comic book Eros Comix has ever published. Warning: violent sexual situations.

The final issue of Elizabeth Bathory comes to a head when Elizabeth attains the throne as the destroyer of the Dark Lord and is crowned the Countess of Blood. One by one, readers are discovering the power behind creator Raulo’s mystic dream of an evil woman in touch with her dark side. This is not an erotic series that is typical of Eros Comix. Yes there is much explicit sex in this series, but the sex is not used to titillate the reader but rather to tell the story of a demoness from Hell and her wants, needs and motivations and how she became a goddess of terror. If you’re looking for a great story, do yourself a favor and pick up a copy ofElizabeth Bathory. Warning! This comic contains much blood and violence and is not for the faint of heart.
